name: Catalogue | "Everyone Carries a Room Inside"
description:
Limited edition of 500 copies.

Articles written by Franz Kafka, Georges Perec, Paul Auster, Robert Walser

___________________________

Loneliness is a major contemporary phenomenon, gaining more and more impact on people’s lives. The exacting urban environment, in the face of social and technological changes, never leaves the individual in peace.

____________________________

Curator: Raphie Etgar 
November 2013
Artists: Sophie Calle | Jesper Just | Josephine Meckseper | Chiharu Shiota | Sharon Etgar | Yael Burstein | Samuel Beckett | Sigal Bergman

____________________________

Bilingual (English & Hebrew) 
119 pages
